replacement /rɪˈpleɪsmənt/

(replacements) 

1. N-UNCOUNT If you refer to the replacement of one thing by another, you mean that the second thing takes the place of the first. 代替; 取代; 更换 [with supp] 

例： ...the replacement of damaged or lost books. …受损或遗失书籍的更换。 

2. N-COUNT Someone who takes someone else's place in an organization, government, or team can be referred to as their replacement . 接替者 

例： Taylor has nominated Adams as his replacement. 泰勒已经提名亚当斯为接替者。

